author: Alexander Pyles
title: Martin O'Malley is latest presidential candidate to call Joe Flacco 'elite'
text:
Martin O'Malley is latest presidential candidate to call Joe Flacco 'elite' Ravens' Flacco on working with different receivers 
"It's going to be a little bit challenging for us on offense, but it's just the way it is," Joe Flacco said about working with different receivers. "We wouldn't want it any other way." (Kevin Richardson) 
"It's going to be a little bit challenging for us on offense, but it's just the way it is," Joe Flacco said about working with different receivers. "We wouldn't want it any other way." (Kevin Richardson) Martin O'Malley and Donald Trump both say Joe Flacco is an elite quarterback. 
Joe Flacco probably didn't expect to be such a prominent topic on the campaign trail. 
Former Maryland Gov. Martin O'Malley, in response to a question on Twitter, gave the only answer he could when @PFTCommenter asked O'Malley about the Ravens quarterback. 
"Joe Flacco is definitely an #elite #quarterback," O'Malley wrote . 
Just last month, Flacco was endorsed by Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump . 
"I think Joe Flacco is actually a very elite quarterback," Trump said . "He won a Super Bowl. He did it, really to a certain extent, with that great arm of his. I would say absolutely he is an elite quarterback." 
For a quarterback who often plays in the shadow of the likes of Peyton Manning, Tom Brady, Aaron Rodgers and many others, Flacco sure frequently finds his name coming out of the mouth of politicans on a national stage. 
Last December, President Barack Obama accidentally referred to actor James Franco as "James Flacco" while talking about threats and hacks that led to one of Franco's films, "The Interview," to be removed from theaters. 
As Baltimore Sun reporter Jon Meoli noted then, the Internet immediately asked if "James Flacco" was elite . 
With the Ravens' top two receivers likely to be sidelined by injury for this weekend's game against the Cleveland Browns at M&T Bank Stadium, Flacco might need to prove O'Malley and Trump right for the Ravens to improve to 2-3.
